snippet.title: Calculate your PC's energy use
snippet.description: Microsoft's free Joulemeter utility gives you a rough estimate of a Windows system's power consumption. Plus: tips for reducing your electronics energy bill.

snippet.title: V-Moda Remix Remote in-ear headphones
snippet.description: The V-Moda Remix Remote headphones earn our Editors' Choice recommendation with a colorfully dynamic sound profile, a generous two-year replacement warranty, and a handful of accessories that ensure a tight seal and versatile usability.

snippet.title: Facebook's revamped News Feed: The new normal
snippet.description: How do you know when the news feed revolution is over? When they all start to look the same.

snippet.title: 2013 BMW xDrive35i
snippet.description: The 2013 BMW X6 xDrive35i isn't a bad sports SUV, but its emphasis of form over function makes it the least appealing of BMW's SUVs.

snippet.title: 2013 BMW X1 xDrive28i
snippet.description: It's not a driver aid powerhouse, but the 2013 BMW xDrive28i with the M Sport package is a driver's car with great handling and a spartan yet premium feel.

snippet.title: Artist seeks crowdfunding for normal-looking Barbie
snippet.description: Everyone knows Barbie isn't real. In any sense of the word. Now a designer wants to introduce a whole line of Barbies that look like, well, women.

snippet.title: G-Form Xtreme iPhone 5 case
snippet.description: The company has released its iPhone 5 and Galaxy S3 cases and unveils new cases for the iPad, iPad Mini, and iPod Touch.

snippet.title: 2013 Honda Accord Coupe
snippet.description: The 2013 Honda Accord Coupe EX-L V-6 is a big step in the right direction for Honda, with great performance and good tech, but we worry that all of these virtues may not trickle down to the rest of the brand.

snippet.title: Apple engineer: We wanted to make a phone for 'normal people'
snippet.description: In an Apple v. Samsung patent case, an engineer who worked on the first iPhone's user interface talks the jury through the development of the device and Apple's steps to make it user-friendly.

snippet.title: China, U.S. to form working group on cyberspying issue
snippet.description: After a meeting with China Foreign Minister Wang Yi, U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry says the two countries have agreed to work toward cybersecurity for both nations.
